President Joseph R. Biden has issued a proclamation on Armed Forces Day, expressing appreciation for the service and sacrifices of the members of the Army, Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps, Space Force, Coast Guard, and National Guard and Reserve forces. The proclamation recognizes the duty to properly support and equip troops both during their service and after they return home, as well as their families, caregivers, and survivors. The President's administration focuses on key issues such as supporting veterans, addressing mental health challenges, combating the opioid epidemic, and fighting cancer. The administration also aims to address toxic exposures and environmental hazards faced by service members, as well as sexual harassment and assault in the military. Efforts are being made to promote diversity, equal opportunity, and inclusivity in the armed forces. President Biden calls upon all Americans to observe and appreciate Armed Forces Day by displaying the flag and participating in local events.